{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Security Leak Scanner",
  "description": "Scans generated code for security issues. Lists all findings with severity, then automatically fixes high-priority or critical security leaks.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "IMPORTANT: Skip this analysis entirely if the only edited files are under `.kiro/specs/`, `docs/`, or are documentation markdown files (README.md, AGENT.md, CLAUDE.md, QUICK_START.md, GITHUB_SUBMISSION.md). Only analyze actual source code changes.\n\nReview changed files for potential security issues. Follow this two-phase process:\n\n**Phase 1 — List all findings with severity:**\nScan for these issues and list each with a severity (🔴 Critical, 🟡 Warning, 🟢 Info):\n- Hardcoded API keys, tokens, or credentials in source code\n- Private keys or sensitive credentials\n- Encryption keys or certificates\n- Authentication tokens or session IDs\n- Passwords or secrets in configuration files\n- IP addresses containing sensitive data\n- Hardcoded internal URLs\n- Database connection credentials\n- Insecure defaults or missing input validation\n\nPresent the full list before making any changes.\n\n**Phase 2 — Auto-fix critical items only:**\nAutomatically fix ONLY 🔴 Critical severity issues (hardcoded secrets, exposed credentials, leaked keys). Replace them with environment variables, config references, or placeholder values following security best practices. Leave 🟡 Warning and 🟢 Info items as suggestions. After fixing, briefly note which critical items were fixed and why."
  }
}